 governmental practitioners and non-state organisational leaders, this volume offers a rich comparative analysis of de-radicalisation processes from around the world. It answers the questions of when, why and how collective de-radicalisation happens, and it deepens our understanding of this as a means of preventing violent extremism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aRadicalsxRehabilitation. 0aTerroristsxRehabilitation. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh1 aAlmustafa, Hamzah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAshour, Omar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClubb, Gordon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHutcheon, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Thomas H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasrils, Ronnie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarchesi, Aldo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartín Álvarez, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRushdi, Osama, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaeed, Haider, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Thula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaddele Maru, Mehari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147446714840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474467148423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474467148/original  a978-3-11-07804